OL,3,CPub landlord returns to La Folie Inn
OL,4,C20 years since its closure
OL,6,F"I think the rest of it should be a
OL,7,Ffish eatery but I don't mean a posh
OL,8,Fnosh place, but a place where people
OL,9,Fwould come and expect the catch of the
OL,10,Fday to be freshly cooked for them."
OL,12,FA part of Chris will always live on in
OL,13,Fthis bar and although his days of
OL,14,Fbeing the pub landlord are long gone,
OL,15,Fhe hopes one day someone else will
OL,16,Ftake the helm.
OL,18,FHe concluded: "It's sad but next time
OL,19,FI see it, maybe it'll be resurrected
OL,20,Finto something different.
